    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine sancte et individue trinitatis. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/173">Otto</persName> divina annuente clementia <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus. Si ratis fidelium nostrorum
                        petitionibus assensum prebemus, fideliores [eos] nobis fore non dubitamus.
                        Idcirco omnium fidelium sancte dei ecclesie nostrorumque fidelium presentium
                        scilicet ac futurorum noverit universitas, qualiter nos <rs
                            key="#Intercessory">consultu ac interventu</rs><persName
                            key="#Intercessory #Archpriests"> Adeldac</persName>
                        <rs key="#Archpriests">archipresulis</rs> summique regnorum nostrorum
                        consiliarii venerabili <rs key="#Bishops">episcopo</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Cities #Mother_churches" ref="#places/1848">Bellunensis <rs
                                key="#Cities">civitatis</rs></placeName> nostroque dilecto <rs
                            key="#fidelisOf">fideli</rs> per huius precepti paginam donamus
                        concedimus atque largimur <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure"
                            >aliquantam terram iuris regni nostri</rs> coniacentem in <geogName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/512"><placeName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#places/629"><rs key="#Comitatus">comitatu</rs>
                                Cenetensi</placeName></geogName>, in loco <placeName
                            key="#Rivers #Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/947">Obederzo</placeName>
                        <rs
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >duas massaricias regales</rs> de <placeName
                            key="#Rivers #Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Saxora</placeName> firmante in <rs key="#Rivers">Plaui</rs> sicut
                        currit <rs key="#Rivers">Plauesella</rs> inter <rs key="#Rivers"
                            >Liquentiam</rs> et de &lt;...> firmante in <placeName
                            key="#Rivers #Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Fossadio</placeName> seu a <geogName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Castle"
                            ref="#estates/544"><placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Castle"
                                ref="#places/944"><rs
                                    key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Castle"
                                    >castello</rs> Paucinico</placeName></geogName> cum <rs
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >duabus massariciis regalibus</rs> de <placeName
                            key="#Mountains #Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Mention #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/946"><rs
                                key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention">monte
                                Cauallo </rs></placeName><rs key="#Boundary_settings">firmante</rs>
                        in <placeName key="#Boundary_settings" ref="#places/945"
                            >Cauulano</placeName> seu vero de <placeName
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Paterno</placeName> firmante in flumine Liquentia, et <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">terram</rs> que fuit de <persName
                            key="#Deacons"><name ref="Audivertus">Audeuirto</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Deacons">diacono</rs>, que iacet in <placeName
                            key="#Mountains #Landed_possessions"><rs key="#Mountains">valle</rs>
                            Lapacinense</placeName>, una cum omnibus pertinentiis earum que modo in
                        illa terra vel que inantea deo adiuvante iam dictus episcopus Iohannes habet
                        vel acquirere potest, tam ex <rs key="#Castle">castellis</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Curtes">curtis</rs> hedificiis quamque <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">terris</rs>
                        <rs key="#Cereals">agris campis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Hay/fodder">pratis pascuis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Forests">silvis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Wine">vineis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Rivers">aquis aquarumque decursibus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Mills">molendinis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Fisheries">piscationibus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Wood">salectis</rs><rs key="#Mountains"> montibus alpibus
                            planiciebus</rs> mobilibus et inmobilibus rebus ad praedictam terram
                        iuste et legaliter pertinentibus que dici vel nominari possunt, ex integro,
                        ut iam praediximus, <rs key="#Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure">de nostro
                            imperiali iure et dominio in ius et dominium</rs> praefati episcopi
                            <persName key="#Bishops #fidelisOf">Iohannis</persName> donamus atque
                        largimur, ut iure hereditario habeat teneat firmiterque possideat habeatque
                        potestatem tenendi dandi vendendi commutandi pro anima iudicandi et quicquid
                        eius animus exinde decreverit faciendi, post suum vero discessum deveniat in
                            <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Profits_of_justice #Right_to_fortify #Bishops"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1417"><rs key="#Mother_churches">ecclesiam</rs>
                            sancti Martini</orgName>, nostra nostrorumque successorum et omnium
                        hominum controversia remota. Insuper etiam concessimus eidem venerabili
                        episcopo Iohanni dilectoque nostro fideli per nostram imperialem
                        auctoritatem ut in praedicta terra quam ei per praeceptum donavimus, in
                        quibuscumque locis sibi placeat, <rs key="#Right_to_fortify">castella turres
                            et merula hedificare et fossas facere habeat potestatem</rs>, et ut
                        nullus <rs key="#Marquis/duke">dux</rs>
                        <rs key="#Marquis/duke">marchio</rs>
                        <rs key="#Count">comes</rs>
                        <rs key="#Viscount">vicecomes</rs> vel <rs key="#Missus">missus</rs>
                        discurrens seu quilibet <rs key="#Other_minor_officer">rei publice exactor
                            vel iudex</rs> homines super prescriptam [terram] residentes vel
                        habitantes ad nullum placitum distringere presumat, sed liceat episcopo
                        eiusque <rs key="#Advocatus_of_other_public_authorities">advocato</rs>
                        <rs key="#Profits_of_justice">placitum</rs> super eos tenere omnesque
                        illorum causas legitime finire, omnium hominum contradictione remota. Si
                        quis igitur huius nostri praecepti ac donationis nec non et concessionis
                        violator vel contemptor extiterit, sciat se compositurum <rs key="#Penalty"
                            >auri optimi libras centum</rs>, medietatem <rs key="#Camera_regis"
                            >camere nostre </rs>et medietatem praefato episcopo Iohanni Bellunensis
                        civitatis vel cui ipse dederit vel habere statuerit. Quod ut verius credatur
                        et diligentius ab omnibus observetur, hanc praecepti paginam exinde
                        conscribi iussimus, manu propria roborantes anulo nostro in calce sigillari
                        iussimus. Signum domni Ottonis magni et invictissimi (M.) imperatoris
                        augusti. <persName key="#Chancellor">Liutgerius</persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> advicem <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Bishops">Vidonis</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopi</rs> et <rs key="#Archchancellor"
                            >archicancellarii</rs> recognovi et subscripsi. Data quarto idus
                        septembris anno dominice incarnationis DCCCCLXIII, indictione sexta, anno
                        imperii magni Ottonis imperatoris augusti secundo; actum in <rs
                            key="#Mountains">monte</rs> Feretri ad petram sancti Leonis. </ab>
                </div>
